Result<T> is implemented as a struct with three fields:
  {
    T:val,           // The success value (or ERR sentinel if error)
    void*:err,       // Error message pointer (NULL if no error, non-NULL if error)
    bool:is_error    // Error flag (false = success, true = error)
  }

LLVM IR representation:
  %Result = type { <value_type>, ptr, i1 }
  Example: Result<int32> = { i32, ptr, i1 }

// Function declaration - return type is the SUCCESS type
func:divide = int32(int32:a, int32:b) {
    if (b == 0) {
        fail(-1);  // Returns Result<int32> with error state
    }
    pass(a / b);   // Returns Result<int32> with success value
};

// Internally becomes:
// Result<int32> (set is_error=false, val=result, err=NULL)
// Result<int32> (set is_error=true, val=ERR, err=error_msg)

Example:
func:get_five = int32() {
    pass(5);  // Returns Result<int32>{val=5, err=NULL, is_error=false}
};

